OverTheWire Bandit – Level 30 → Level 31 
Level Goal
A git repository is hosted at:
 ssh://bandit30-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org/home/bandit30-git/repo on port 2220.
The password for user bandit30-git is the same as the password for bandit30.

Commands Used
git clone
ls
cat

Steps
SSH into the Bandit server.
Use the bandit30 password to connect as user bandit30-git:
  ssh bandit30-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
Clone the repository located at /home/bandit30-git/repo:
  git clone ssh://bandit30-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:2220/home/bandit30-git/repo
Navigate into the cloned repository directory:
  cd repo
List files and inspect contents to find the password for bandit31:
  ls -la
  cat <file-containing-password>

Result
Successfully retrieved the password for bandit31 from the cloned git repository.

What I Learned
Connecting to remote git repositories over SSH with custom ports.
Using git clone to explore repository contents.
Searching for hidden or sensitive information inside git repositories during security challenges.
